Subject: obsolete aggregate of major administrative subdivisions
aggregate of governmental organizations
Value:
An aggregate of organizations that is not itself a governmental organization, has only governmental organizations as members, and has at least two governmental organizations as members.
@en

Subject: subnational entity
Value: a governmental organization that has a local, regional, or territorial government that recognizes a sovereign state as its higher political authority@en

Subject: nongovernmental organization
Value: a geopolitical organization that is voluntary and private, whose members are individual persons or organizations that come together to acheive a common purpose.@en

Subject: intergovernmental organization
Value: an intergovernmental organization that has at least three member states, that has activies in at least three states, and that is unified by some formal intergovernmental agreement
